news.title: Navi Mumbai: Cidco announces scheme to sell 243 shops in Ulwe housing complex
news.para: The shops have been made available for the small and medium businesses in Ulwe node which is now well connected with varied modes of transportation.

news.title: Hyderabad: Two held for Rs 7 crore real estate fraud
news.para: ​Police said that MD of JJ Infra Pvt Ltd, T Venkata Ramana Prasad, and his marketing agent K Venkata Ratnam, were arrested after complainants from several victims.

news.title: Vizag steel plant gets Rs 243 crore through sale of land blocks or plots
news.para: RINL properties located at HB Colony near Seetammadhara, Autonagar, and Pedagantyada in the city were put on auction on March 14 and March 15.

news.title: Tamil Nadu apartment ownership law toothless without rules
news.para: The delay in forming rules for the Tamil Nadu Apartment Ownership Act hinders Chennai's apartment complexes' redevelopment, impacting developers and residents' associations seeking clarity and legal remedies for opposing residents.

news.title: Early property taxpayers to get 10% rebate next FY: Guwahati mayor
news.para: The mayor said the property owners who will pay the property taxes in the first two months of the next financial year, between April 1 and May 31 in the next fiscal, will get 10% rebate on property tax.

news.title: Delhi LG nod may help convert industrial plots into freeholds
news.para: The LG has granted an ‘in principle’ approval to the proposal for the extension subject to several conditions, it added.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body razes 439 illegal structures
news.para: As per the TSbPASS rules, the special task force at zonal office level, headed by zonal commissioner, was constituted to detect and monitor unauthorised constructions, unauthorised layouts and take timely enforcement action.

news.title: High buildings in Visakhapatnam must have fire safety system: Municipal commissioner
news.para: In an official statement, the commissioner emphasized that this is mandatory for public safety and security. He further said that the staff in the concerned establishments should be trained to handle firefighting equipments and respond to emergencies.

news.title: Bengaluru: BWSSB says builders using drinking water for construction will lose NOC
news.para: BWSSB chairman Ram Prasath Manohar has issued a public notification in this regard, stating that builders should compulsorily use tre ated water for construction purposes.

news.title: Now low-height streetlight poles in Noida for better visibility
news.para: As against the normal pole of 15 to 25 feet, now poles of 13 to 20 feet will be installed which are 2 to 5 feet lower. While the cost of these poles ranges from Rs 2000 to Rs 4000, the cost is about 30-35% less than the normal-size poles.

news.title: Panvel civic body records highest single day property tax recovery of Rs 2.25 crore
news.para: The civic body has so far recovered Rs 283 crore property tax this fiscal year. The total recovery stands at Rs 569 crore as of Friday. The recovery may rise as the financial year is approaching its closure within a fortnight.

news.title: Civic body to carry out 3D mapping of Mumbai
news.para: The project aims to create a digital twin of the city using advanced geo-spatial technology and artificial intelligence, covering 500 sq km of Mumbai, to enable better administration, planned infrastructure development, removal of unauthorised construction and help in disaster management.

news.title: Rajasthan housing minister inaugurates six projects of RHB
news.para: ​In addition, the minister also inaugurated 12 residential projects together comprising 3,001 tenements in various cities across the state.

news.title: DDA to develop three jhuggi clusters in east Delhi
news.para: ​These JJ Clusters include Kalandar Colony, Deepak Colony and Dilshad Vihar Colony that house nearly 4,000 households.

news.title: Odisha RERA directs builders to ensure safety & security of workers
news.para: ORERA stated the safety and security of construction workers is a major issue in the real estate sector. This matter is being flagged up at the national and international levels, the letter read.

news.title: Developed India by 2047 will need highly matured, developed real estate sector: Housing minister
news.para: "A developed India by 2047 will also require a highly matured and developed real estate sector, both in the residential and the commercial segment," Puri said.

news.title: HC stays RERA takeover by Punjab government
news.para: The petitioner claimed that Rera Punjab had been superseded by the impugned order of March 12 for four months or till the quorum is complete under Section 82 of the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act, 2016.

news.title: Set up special cell to hear complaints of senior citizens on delays in redevelopment: Bombay HC
news.para: A bench of Justices Girish Kulkarni and Firdosh Pooniwalla was given the state housing department’s March 4 circular that set out measures (see graphic) to be taken in such cases.

news.title: US: National Association of Realtors to pay $418 million to settle lawsuits
news.para: The $418 million settlement calls for the National Association of Realtors to eliminate decades-old rules on commissions, and make it easier for buyers to negotiate fees with their own agents or use no agents at all.

news.title: Delhi HC asks Unitech's founder to surrender, refuses to extend interim bail in ED case
news.para: ​Justice Anoop Kumar Mendiratta observed that the petitioner was embroiled in serious offences involving diversion of over Rs 5,000 crore belonging to home buyers, who were "duped" and are now shelterless.
